						               													<description>A family of cowardly ogres, a journey to overcome their fears and the awareness that they must do it together.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;These are just some of the elements of this cooperative game.&amp;#10;The children will have to move on the board and - by drawing &amp;quot;Courage&amp;quot; and &amp;quot;Talk about it&amp;quot; cards - overcome and beat the fears of the group: let's help each other and neutralize the different fears by telling and finding shared solutions.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Only by talking, interacting and collaborating the whole De Orchis family will reach the finish line and defeat the small and big daily fears that affect each of us.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Narration and cooperative play allow adults to gently approach the emotional world of the little ones and help them to express themselves by offering a lot of ideas on how many times it is possible to overcome their fears with ease, especially if you decide to share them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The active player rolls the die and moves his token clockwise by as many squares as the result. Depending on the square where the movement ends, he draws a &amp;quot;Courage&amp;quot; card, a &amp;quot;Talk about it&amp;quot; card, a Fear card or immediately plays another turn. After moving the token, you can decide to use either a &amp;quot;Talk about it&amp;quot; or a &amp;quot;Courage&amp;quot; card to remove a Fear card in play. The turn passes to the next player.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;You win all together only if you have removed all the Fear cards in play. If the players decide to stop the game, surrender, resign or run out of cards, the game is lost.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
